;; agent SEMA plane schema — daemon-owned.
;;
;; The agent daemon's provider registry (the policy state: which providers are
;; configured, the default) is held in the engine and configured through the
;; meta tier's component-owned `handle_meta_connection` hook, mirroring cloud's
;; Store. So this SEMA plane is honestly stateless: the durable-redb projection
;; of the provider registry is DEFERRED (the registry is in-memory until a
;; restart, then re-supplied by meta Configure). The plane exists to satisfy the
;; uniform three-plane shape.

{}
[WriteInput ReadInput]
[WriteOutput ReadOutput]
{
  WriteInput [(NoDurableState NoDurableState)]
  NoDurableState Stateless

  ReadInput [(NoDurableState NoDurableState)]

  WriteOutput [(Stateless Stateless)]
  ReadOutput [(Stateless Stateless)]

  Stateless { }
}
